div.div: How to fix VS Code integrated terminal choppy and laggy on macOS Big Sur?

June 2024 update If you're experiencing this recently it could be because of a recent update. You can fix it by either: Option 1: Updating VSCode to the Latest Version A fix was included in v1.90.1 Option 2: Disabling shellIntegration If the issue persists, as it seems to be the case for some folks, you can temporarily fix it by adding the following setting in settings.json : terminal.integrated.shellIntegration.enabled: false
terminal.integrated.shellIntegration.enabled :
Determines whether or not shell integration is auto-injected to support features like enhanced command tracking and current working directory detection.
